A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing the centennial anniversary of the John D. Archbold Memorial Hospital in
2 Thomasville, Georgia; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, in 1923, John F. Archbold purchased a 5.81-acre parcel on Gordon Avenue for
4 the construction of a new hospital for Thomasville and Thomas County; and
5 WHEREAS, in 1923, a Board of Trustees was formed, a charter of incorporation was
6 obtained, and a hospital director was selected; and
7 WHEREAS, the John D. Archbold Memorial Hospital was dedicated on June 30, 1925, and
8 accepted its first patient in transfer from the City Hospital on July 3, 1925; and
9 WHEREAS, the John D. Archbold Memorial Hospital has steadfastly maintained its status
10 as a leading medical facility in Southwest Georgia, offering cancer, surgical, heart, imaging,
11 maternity, and primary care; and
12 WHEREAS, the John D. Archbold Memorial Hospital has maintained a position at the
13 forefront of medical research and investigation on a level that vastly supersedes the
14 expectations for a community hospital; and
